## New Backend system

Have a small backend to store images, template metadata for article creation 

It will also be used to organize and manage the type of articles we have.\\

### Slim and optimal 

Our budget isnt as big as we want to , so finding  a craetive way to store these articles , images, members ,etc is the desired choice 

### Box folder 

As of now, indigo uses our school box folder to manage nad store our images, tet, assets, etc. is there a way to integrate box as a sort of backend where we keep those files and images there, in an organized an systematic matter, and then our front end or backend grabs then and displays them. If its backend then im thinking of  a server that fetches the content from box folder, and then delivers it to the front end website. 

### Archive 

Having a standeradized organization system, we will be able to preserve and archive pieces of writings so no article gets lost when a new set of officers come in. 

### Scalable and self maintained

Once having a set way to add articles, publish them on the website, market them, all without a developer manually doing it, expanding our writing department will be alot easier. 

#### Bottle neck 

Right now our article groups require one dev to handle one piece of writing  
As I have been hearing an increased interest in publishing writings outside of articles, our current system would require to match each new article with a dev member . 

* Not sustainable   
* Busy work for devs  
  * Not aligned with industry work k
